      <p class="header-eyebrow">The Lab</p>
      <h1 class="header-title">Now</h1>
      <p class="header-meta">Last updated: May 11, 2026.</p>
    </header>

    <article class="article-body">
      <p><strong>Phase 8</strong> of the research program is starting: a rank-r interpolation scan of the bulk-state space, scanning between the product class (rank 1) and the Haar class (rank <span class="math-inline">d<sub>eff</sub></span>). The prediction from Paper 1 is a smooth interpolation between the <span class="math-inline">d<sub>B</sub><sup>-1/2</sup></span> and <span class="math-inline">d<sub>B</sub><sup>-3/2</sup></span> exponents. A phase transition at some critical rank would be a surprise and an interesting physics statement.</p>

      <p>First data expected within a week. Updates here as they arrive.</p>

      <div class="section-rule"><div class="section-rule-line"></div></div>

      <h2 class="article-subhead">Previous phases</h2>
      <p>Phases 1 through 7 cleared the gate conditions for Paper 1. All phase memos are available in <a href="/lab/phase-memos">The Phase Memos</a>.</p>

      <p>Paper 1, <em>Complexity-Sensitive Complementarity in Non-Isometric Holographic Codes</em>, is submitted. The full record of the work is in <a href="/field-notes">Field Notes</a> and <a href="/lab/code-and-data">Code and Data</a>.</p>
    </article>
  </main>
</Base>
